text: Abutalipovo (, ) is a rural locality (a village) in Artakulsky Selsoviet of Karaidelsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 261 . There are 7 streets. == Ethnicity == The village is inhabited by Tatars. == Geography == It is located 45 km from Karaidel, 4 km from Artakul. == References == Category:Rural localities in Karaidelsky District
title: Abutalipovo
